For APIs that need a POST request with the user/pw contained in the body, InvokeHTTP currently uses flowfile content to populate the body. However flowfile content cannot be set with sensitive parameters and so there is no way to hide those values. The approach here is to put that information within processors in a process group and then that process group could have its access control set so only those with rights to see that process group could view those contents.
Currently I have a feature request open for the need to be able to set the body content with sensitive values and the moderators agreed in the comments that it is something that should be incorporated in a future release of the InvokeHTTP processor.
(More details at https://issues.apache.org/jira/projects/NIFI/issues/NIFI-11331?filter=allopenissues)
